    <stitle>CE 200, CE 300 - HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - Install</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Install</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Bumper</title>
            <para>With an assistant, locate the bumper assembly with safety gate attached and carry the bumper to the
                bus chassis.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0900976" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900976.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 90. Front Bumper Install</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. BUMPER TOP MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. BUMPER LOWER MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With an assistant, place bumper at bumper mounting brackets, align bumper mounting holes
                    with mounting holes in mounting bracket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert bolts in the upper holes (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900976">Figure 90, Item 1</hotlnk>): one driver side, one passenger side. Hand
                    tighten.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the lower bumper mounting holes and insert lower bolts, and hand tighten.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Finish tightening the bumper bolts to the required torque values.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Torque bumper bolts to 50 to 55 LBF-FT (68 to 75 Nm).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reconnect the appropriate harness connections as required.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
